### PUT vs PATCH

PUT replaces the entire resource with the provided data, while PATCH applies partial updates. Use PUT when sending complete data, PATCH for partial modifications.

```typescript
// PUT - replace entire user
fetch('/api/users/1', {
  method: 'PUT',
  body: JSON.stringify({ name: 'John', email: 'john@example.com' })
});

// PATCH - update only name
fetch('/api/users/1', {
  method: 'PATCH',
  body: JSON.stringify({ name: 'John' })
});
```

**Common interview trap:** Thinking PATCH is always smaller in payload—it's about intent, not size.

