### HTTP 204 No Content

204 indicates the request succeeded but there's no content to return to the client. Use it for successful DELETE operations or when you don't need to send a response body.

```typescript
// Delete resource and return 204
app.delete('/api/posts/:id', (req, res) => {
  removePost(req.params.id);
  res.status(204).send(); // No body needed
});

// vs 200 with empty body
res.status(200).json({}); // Less appropriate
```

**Common interview trap:** Confusing 204 with 404—204 means success with no content, 404 means not found.

