### Caching Header Strategy

ETag is a hash-based validator for conditional requests (304 Not Modified), Last-Modified is time-based validation, and Cache-Control manages cache lifetime. ETag detects content changes reliably, Last-Modified is simpler but less precise, and Cache-Control prevents unnecessary requests by setting expiration.

```typescript
app.get('/api/data', (req, res) => {
  const data = JSON.stringify({id: 1, name: 'John'});
  const etag = crypto.createHash('md5').update(data).digest('hex');
  res.set('ETag', etag);
  res.set('Cache-Control', 'public, max-age=3600');
  res.set('Last-Modified', new Date().toUTCString());
  if (req.get('If-None-Match') === etag) return res.status(304).send();
  res.json({id: 1, name: 'John'});
});
```

**Common interview trap:** Thinking ETag and Last-Modified serve the same purpose—they work together for robust validation.

answer.ru:
