### API Versioning Strategies

Path-based versioning (/v1/users) is explicit, cacheable by CDNs, and easier to debug; header-based (Accept: application/vnd.api+v2+json) keeps URLs clean but is invisible in logs. Choose path-based for public APIs where clients may lag, headers for internal APIs prioritizing URL elegance.

```typescript
// Path-based
app.get('/v1/users', (req, res) => res.json({version: 1, data: []}));
app.get('/v2/users', (req, res) => res.json({version: 2, data: [], pagination: {}}));

// Header-based
app.get('/users', (req, res) => {
  const version = req.get('Accept')?.includes('v2') ? 2 : 1;
  res.set('Content-Type', `application/vnd.api+v${version}+json`);
  res.json({version, data: []});
});
```

**Common interview trap:** Believing one approach is universally better—choose based on API maturity and client diversity.

answer.ru:
