### CORS and Preflight Requests

CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) allows controlled cross-origin requests. Preflight OPTIONS requests validate whether the browser should send the actual request. Use `Access-Control-Allow-Origin`, `Access-Control-Allow-Credentials`, `Access-Control-Allow-Methods`, and `Access-Control-Allow-Headers` to control access securely.

```typescript
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  res.set('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', 'https://trusted-domain.com');
  res.set('Access-Control-Allow-Credentials', 'true');
  res.set('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET,POST,PUT,DELETE');
  res.set('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type,Authorization');
  res.set('Access-Control-Max-Age', '86400');
  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') return res.sendStatus(204);
  next();
});
```

**Common interview trap:** Setting `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` with credentials=true—this is a security violation.

