### ETag vs Last-Modified

ETag is a hash-based validator for the entire response body, while Last-Modified is timestamp-based. ETags are stronger validators but require more computation; Last-Modified is simpler but fails when content changes without modification time updates.

```typescript
// ETag approach - strong validator
res.set('ETag', '"abc123"');
if (req.headers['if-none-match'] === '"abc123"') {
  res.status(304).send(); // Not Modified
}

// Last-Modified approach
res.set('Last-Modified', new Date('2024-01-15').toUTCString());
if (new Date(req.headers['if-modified-since']) >= new Date('2024-01-15')) {
  res.status(304).send();
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Thinking ETag and Last-Modified are mutually exclusive—use both for maximum compatibility.

