### API Versioning Strategies

URI versioning (/v1/users) is most explicit but creates URL sprawl. Header-based versioning (Accept: application/vnd.api+json;version=1) is cleaner but less discoverable. Content negotiation is RESTful but complex to implement and test.

```typescript
// URI versioning - explicit
app.get('/v1/users/:id', (req, res) => { /* v1 logic */ });
app.get('/v2/users/:id', (req, res) => { /* v2 logic */ });

// Header versioning - cleaner
app.get('/users/:id', (req, res) => {
  const version = req.headers['api-version'] || '1';
  if (version === '2') { /* v2 logic */ }
});
```

**Common interview trap:** Not considering backward compatibility—always maintain at least two versions simultaneously.

