### CORS and Preflight Requests

CORS allows browsers to make cross-origin requests safely. For non-simple requests (PUT, DELETE, custom headers), browsers send an OPTIONS preflight to verify the server allows the operation. This prevents malicious scripts from making unauthorized requests.

```typescript
// Server-side CORS setup
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  res.set('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', 'https://example.com');
  res.set('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, PUT, DELETE');
  res.set('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type, Authorization');
  res.set('Access-Control-Max-Age', '3600');
  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') res.sendStatus(200);
  else next();
});
```

**Common interview trap:** Allowing wildcard origins (*) with credentials—this is a security vulnerability.

answer.ru:
