### Distributed Tracing with OpenTelemetry

OpenTelemetry instruments applications to create spans (measurements) for each operation, forming traces that show request flow across services. Span contexts (trace ID, span ID, flags) are propagated via HTTP headers (traceparent, tracestate) to correlate requests across service boundaries. This reveals bottlenecks: which service is slow, which databases are queried, and where latency accumulates.

```typescript
// OpenTelemetry span context propagation
const { trace, context } = require('@opentelemetry/api');
const tracer = trace.getTracer('my-service');

app.get('/api/users/:id', (req, res) => {
  const span = tracer.startSpan('getUser');
  context.with(trace.setSpan(context.active(), span), () => {
    // Downstream service call includes traceparent header
    fetch('http://db-service/users/' + req.params.id, {
      headers: { 'traceparent': getTraceParent() } // Propagate context
    });
    span.end();
  });
});
```

**Common interview trap:** Assuming trace IDs must be manually generated—most frameworks auto-inject them if properly configured; just propagate existing headers.

answer.ru:
